{{Use British English|date=July 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2018}} {{Infobox company | name = Coktel Vision | logo = Coktel Vision (1999) Logo.jpeg | type = [[Subsidiary]] | industry = [[Video game industry]] | fate = Merged into [[Mindscape]] | founded = {{Start date and age|df=yes|1984}} | founder = Roland Oskian | defunct = {{End date|df=yes|2005|10|21}} | hq_location_city = [[Paris]] | hq_location_country = France | parent = {{Unbulleted list|[[Sierra On-Line]] {{small|(1994–1996)}}|[[Vivendi Games]] {{small|(1996–2005)}}|[[Mindscape]] {{small|(2005)}}}} }}
'''Coktel Vision''' (also known as '''Coktel''' or '''Coktel Studio''') was a French [[video game publisher]] based in [[Paris]]. The company was founded in 1984 by Roland Oskian, a former executive of [[Matra Espace]].<ref name="Sierra">{{cite web |url=https://www.lesechos.fr/04/05/1994/LesEchos/16638-099-ECH_l-americain-sierra-on-line-absorbe-coktel-vision.htm |title=L'américain Sierra-On-Line absorbe Coktel Vision - Les Echos |author= |date= |website=www.lesechos.fr |accessdate=22 July 2018}}</ref> The company was acquired by American publisher [[Sierra On-Line]] on 4 May 1994.<ref name="Sierra" /> On 21 February 1996, Sierra On-Line, including Coktel Vision, was acquired by [[CUC International]] and became part of CUC's new [[CUC Software]] (later renamed Vivendi Universal Games) branch.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1996/02/21/business/cuc-will-buy-2-software-companies-for-1.8-billion.html |title=CUC Will Buy 2 Software Companies for $1.8 Billion |first=Peter H. |last=Lewis |date= |website=nytimes.com |accessdate=22 July 2018}}</ref> Vivendi Universal Games proceeded to sell Coktel Vision to [[Mindscape]] on 21 October 2005, wherein eleven employees were absorbed into Mindscape.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamekult.com/actualite/vu-games-cede-coktel-a-mindscape-44419.html |title=VU Games cède Coktel à Mindscape |author= |date=21 October 2005 |website=gamekult.com |accessdate=22 July 2018}}</ref> The Coktel brand name however was retained by Mindscape many years afterwards.
