'''''DSI: Disease Scene Investigation''''' is a children's [[Web series]] produced by the provincial government of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]], for its "Immunize BC" website. An obvious [[pun]] on ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation]]'', it stars [[Yvette Lu]] as a high tech nurse, guiding two high school students through their investigations into infectious diseases threatening their high school. The series, co-produced by TSTP productions and the [[Provincial Health Services Authority (British Columbia)]], is designed to teach children and parents in British Columbia about the importance of disease prevention. The series is directed by C. Galloway.<ref>[http://www.immunizebc.ca/ImmVacPrevDis/default.htm Immunize BC: "DSI: Disease Scene Investigation" (web series) Provincial Health Services Authority]</ref><ref>[http://www.yvettelu.com/credits.html Yvette Lu - official site]</ref> The Web series also appears on YouTube.<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/user/immunizebc Immunize BC Channel]</ref>
Actor [[Yvette Lu]], who plays "The Nurse" in the series, is a real-life medical doctor.<ref>[http://www.yvettelu.com/YvetteLu-MingPao-June052010.pdf "Doctor Who Acts -vs- Actor Who Doctors" Ming Pao (Chinese language paper) Ming Pao Newspapers (Canada) Limited. 2010.06.05]</ref>
