The '''Harbor Conservatory for the Performing Arts''' is a [[performing arts center]] in [[Spanish Harlem]], [[New York City]], [[United States|USA]].  It provides performance space and instruction in the disciplines of [[theatre]], [[music]], and [[dance]].<ref name=HarborConservatory>[http://www.harborconservatory.org/ Harbor Conservatory for the Performing Arts<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>  It has been profiled in [[People Magazine]], ''[[The New York Times]]'', ''[[New York Daily News]]'' and in the public television documentary, ''Mi Mambo!''.<ref name=Boricua>[http://www.boricua.com/newyork/Charlie_Palmieri_Scholarship.html Article] on the [[Charlie Palmieri#Scholarship|Charlie Palmieri Memorial Piano Scholarship]] at Boricua.com</ref>  

The Conservatory hosts the annual competition to award the [[Charlie Palmieri#Scholarship|Charlie Palmieri Memorial Piano Scholarship]], a scholarship established in [[Charlie Palmieri|Palmieri]]'s memory by Latin musician [[Tito Puente]] for the benefit of intermediate and advanced young (12–25) pianists' study of Latin-style piano.<ref name=Boricua />

