ef>{{cite news|first=Matthew J. |last=Guerrieri |title=The Neglected Market |url=http://ccat.sas.upenn.edu/annex/italmkt.html |year=1997 |accessdate=2007-10-10 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060918224026/http://ccat.sas.upenn.edu/annex/italmkt.html |archivedate=September 18, 2006 }}</ref> Palumbo’s was destroyed by fire in 1994 and was determined to be arson.<ref> {{cite news |url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=PI&s_site=philly&p_multi=PI&p_theme=realcities&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=0EB2A64A69F92235&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM |title=3D ARSON RULED AT PALUMBO'S |first=Ralph |last=Cipriano |date=1994-09-13 | accessdate=2007-10-10 | work=The Philadelphia Inquirer}} </ref> The site, marked by an unofficial historical plaque, is now occupied by a chain drug store.<ref name="Dubin">{{cite book | last = Dubin | first = Murray | authorlink = | title = South Philadelphia; Mummers, memories, and the Melrose Diner | publisher = [[Temple University Press]] | date = June 1996 | location = | pages = | url = | doi = | id = | isbn = 1-56639-429-5}}</ref>
[[File:WTP E03 AMP 1.jpg|thumb|left|Plaque at the former location of Palumbo's]]
==Entertainment==
In the 1940s and 1950s, Philadelphia was an important pop music center, with many bands and singers being made or broken in the city.<ref name="funsy"> {{cite news |first=Nick |last=Clooney |title=Nightclub debut didn't suit Funsy |url=http://www.cincypost.com/living/1998/cloon071598.html |work=The Cincinnati Post |publisher=E. W. Scripps Company |date=1998-07-15 |accessdate=2007-10-10 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20041127011243/http://www.cincypost.com/living/1998/cloon071598.html |archivedate= 2004-11-27 }} </ref> The 20th Century Club, Ciro's and the opulent, art deco Click Club on Market St. which Frank also owned were significant elements in the music scene.<ref name="funsy"/> Benny Goodman And His Orchestra with Patti Page and pianist Teddy Wilson performed a Live 1946 radio broadcast for the 'One Night Stand' show at Frank Palumbo's Click Club in Philadelphia.<ref>[https://www.amazon.com/One-Night-Stands-Benny-Goodman/dp/B002G5FLRY CD recording Benny Goodman and His Orchestra "One Night Stands"]</ref> Frequent performers at Palumbo's included [[Frank Sinatra]], [[Sergio Franchi]], [[Louis Prima]], [[Louis Armstrong]], the [[Clooney Sisters]], [[Jimmy Durante]] and "The Godfathers" [Al Martino], comedians and numerous entertainers.<ref name="cedrone" /><ref name="rosie" /><ref name="funsy" /><ref> {{cite web |url=http://www.ralphsrestaurant.com/celebrit.htm |title=Ralph's Has Been A Celebrity Destination for over 100 years |accessdate=2007-10-10 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070930092247/http://www.ralphsrestaurant.com/celebrit.htm <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-30}} </ref><ref> {{cite web |url=http://www.louisprima.com/quotes.html |title=quotes |work=The official web site of Louis Prima}}</ref><ref> {{cite web |url=http://tribes.tribe.net/rosemaryclooney/thread/3460ab6f-5ab3-497d-8c31-1a0ff578c404 |title=Recommended Rosie...and The Clooney Sisters}} </ref> A nightly radio series broadcast concerts from the club, many of which were later released as albums.
Well beyond the club’s heyday, the restaurant remained popular. Sinatra visited the “black tie saloon” frequently<ref name="funsy" /> and Mayor [[Frank Rizzo]] spent most evenings there during his rise to power, years in office and beyond.<ref> {{cite news| url=http://www.philadelphiaweekly.com/view.php?id=10398 |first=Andrea|last=Mitchell |title=Me and Frank |date=2005-09-07|accessdate=2007-10-10 |work=Philadelphia Weekly |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070930020002/http://www.philadelphiaweekly.com/view.php?id=10398 <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> |archivedate = 2007-09-30}}</ref> The banquet hall became a popular cultural tradition for many social groups, business organizations, family celebrations, and special events that were mostly attracted by the reasonable prices, menu items and entertainment. {{citation needed|date=May 2013}}
